	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64589173">The ruling appears to make any decision by an agency on the meaning of a stature subject to legal challenge in court. So the previous (and future) decisions against net neutrality would also be subject to challenge. This is really just another power grab by the Supreme Court to make themselves the final arbiter of almost any decision made by the other two branches of government. They can second guess executive decisions and they can reinterpret laws passed by congress to meet their own preferences. This is similar to the "corporations are persons" rule that allows the courts to intervene to protect the "rights" of corporations.</div>
	</div>

